cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to identify the plurality in second person personal pronouns in English texts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training a model to distinguish between single/plural you, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of distantly-supervised labels, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves training a model to improve accuracy, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of publicly available code and data, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computing and Society).
